This paper presents a novel method for pruning deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) research. The method involves learning per-layer thresholds via gradient descent, which is a technique used in neural network optimization (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of $L_0$ regularization, which is a technique used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and other areas of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
